name: External Wall Framing Checklist
Installer details entered
Installer:
1) All relevant drawings and revision numbers checked and attached.
2) Timber delivery dockets checked and correct on arrival.
All timber dockets attached
3) Timber delivered are well stored and protected.
4) DPC installed, checked, and correct as per specifications.
5) Wall locations checked, correct, and approved as per latest revised drawing.
6) Fixings and hold down bolts checked and correct.
7) All openings (doors/windows, etc) checked, correct and approved.
8) Wall type checked (straight and plumb) and within tolerance.
9) All relevant nogs (service, and special fixtures) installed, checked and correct.
10) Moisture reading checked, recorded and acceptable.
11) All wall framing checks completed and inspections carried out.
12) Report sent to client.

GIB Weatherline
Installer details entered
Installer:
All relevant drawings and revision numbers checked and attached / commented.
Substrate accepted and approval given to start lining.
Correct fixings used and installed at correct centres.
Panels overhang the bottom plate on a concrete slab by 15mm minimum as per Gib Weatherline installation manual.
Correct tape installed over vertical / horizontal joints, corners and openings in accordance with Gib Weatherline installation manual.
General photos, comments and observations during installation.
All lining completed correctly within a specified tolerance, checked and approved.
Gib lining report sent to client
( RAISE REMEDIAL / REQUEST FOR SIGNOFF)
WrapShield
Installer details entered
Installer:
Substrate must be dry, clean and free of any contaminants.
All overlaps must be a minimum of 80mm on horizontal and vertical seams.
Inside and outside vertical corners should be at minimum 150mm of overlap.
All installation must be with the lower courses lapped under the upper courses.
All air bubbles must be smooth out to ensure full adhesion.
Apply VaproLiqui-Flash evenly at least 50mm onto the face and at least 25mm out along all sides of the penetration.
